Diagnosis. Body elongate; pereopods 3–4 present and 1–2 articulate; pereonite 5 generally reaching pereonites 3– 4 length together; male abdomen with 1 pair of lobes and 1–2 pairs of appendages 1–2 articulated; female with a pair of lobes (modified from
Guerra-García, 2004
).
